Title: O0 — Area Rug
Body (HTML): Breathing in the damp air, walking along the shore of Fogo Island, the plush feeling of stepping on the moss. It brought all the memory back when we made the rug O0. Hand-tufted with 100% wool by local textile designer Avis Ho.

Title: D0 — Bar Stool
Body (HTML): Hi Thanks Bye cites the Chinese traditional shapes found in courtyard architecture design as the prime influence for the creation of the geometrically-shaped bar stool D0. It features a handy dot hook for your belongings while sipping at the bar.

Title: V0 — Side Table
Body (HTML): The lily pad: born from the mud but never stained. The simple V0 side table design is manufactured out of cold-rolled powder-coated steel sheets and tubings.

Title: F0 — Floor Lamp
Body (HTML): A poetic interpretation of the moon shining over the Lake Ontario by utilizing a traditional Chinese textile making technique, Hi Thanks Bye's cold steel and organic fringe floor lamp F0 is designed to be an encounter of two cultures.

Title: U0 — Shelf/Divider
Body (HTML): With multiple storage purposes crafted from laser-cut steel sheets, the shelf divider U0 is a sculptural translation of the staggering rock scenery. It is designed with traditional Chinese garden principle "hide/reveal" in mind while maintaining the functionality and versatility of a living space.

Title: R0 — Dining Chair
Body (HTML): The geometric R0 chair pays tribute to the renowned Chinese circle chair with a modern twist. It features a round steel support to the backrest and sinuous tubing armrest.
